'''''Night Mynock''''' was a [[Book/Legends|book]] [[Author/Legends|authored]] by writer [[Rogar Farnoster]]<ref name="HoloNet" /> that had been released by [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].<ref name="Date" /> The [[HoloNet News CoCo District Edition|CoCo District Edition]] of [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]]<ref name="HoloNet" /> on the [[Great ReSynchronization|date]] 13:2:28<ref name="Date" /> ranked it as the fifth best-selling book.<ref name="HoloNet" />

==Behind the scenes==
''Night Mynock'' was mentioned on the [[HoloNet News (original website)|HoloNet News website]] in the [[in-universe]] issue ''[[HoloNet News Vol. 531 45]]'', which was published<ref name="HoloNet" /> on [[February 28]], [[2002]],<ref name="HNN45 date">Per {{JCFCite|url=posts/6042498|board=Literature|thread=The Official HoloNetNews Discussion Thread|user=IAmTheDarkSide|date=2002-03-14|time=5:40 PM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220914072556/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/the-official-holonetnews-discussion-thread.5990764/page-4#post-6042498}}, [[HoloNet News Vol. 531 47|''HoloNet News Vol. 531'' #47]] was released on [[March 14]], [[2002]]. As [[HoloNet News (original website)|HoloNet News]] segments were published weekly, and {{HoloNetNewsWeb|45||A Closer Look}} was published two issues prior, it must have been released on [[February 28]] of the same year.</ref> and written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Paul Ens]].<ref name="HNN Credits">{{HoloNetNewsWeb||credits.html|Credits}}</ref>

